# Trivy ignore file — CVEs triaged/accepted for the Security Scanning gate.
#
# The gate runs with `ignore-unfixed: true`, so it only flags vulnerabilities
# that have an upstream fix. The full scan (all severities, fixed or not) is
# still uploaded to the GitHub Security tab via SARIF for visibility — this
# file only suppresses the specific, reviewed CVEs below so the gate fails on
# NEW / not-yet-triaged fixable findings rather than on this known backlog.
#
# Each entry is a pre-existing dependency CVE whose fix requires a dependency
# upgrade tracked as separate work. The breaking ones (mlflow 2.x -> 3.x,
# Airflow 2.8 -> 3.x) are deferred because upgrading them in this PR would
# break the pipeline/DAG jobs; the rest are scheduled for a dependency-bump
# pass. Remove an ID here once its package is upgraded past the fixed version.

# --- mlflow 2.10.0 ---
# MLflow tracking-server RCE / SSRF / path-traversal / auth CVEs. This repo
# uses MLflow as a client against a local file store and does not expose a
# tracking server, so the server-side CVEs are not reachable in this usage.
# Fixes span 2.22.4 .. 3.11.0; a full MLflow 3 upgrade is tracked separately.
